d I got to know Maureen through BSA circles, for completely different sorts of reasons.  We ran a conference on methodology together, so I got to know her through that.  And I was sitting in her house one night, and I said, \'93
Have you still got that data?\'94  And she said, yes, she had. So I said to her, \'93Well, would you let \'85\'94  And she thought about it for a while, because she\rquote d never actually let anybody else see it, and she \'85
