\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f39\fs22\insrsid1661543\charrsid8421308 Janet:\tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid1661543\charrsid8421308 
Relative youth, anyway!  (LAUGHS)  I think my memory of that period, when it was pretty dark days for sociology, was that other people went round saying, you know, \'93It is the end of the world, as we know it\'94, more or less, and I don\rquote 
t think I ever quite felt that.  I felt that we could fight back.  It might pass, and so on.  I think that, the point is, I\rquote ve noticed this at other points in my life, because of the parti
cular trajectory that my adult life took in my twenties, I never really decided that I was going to have an academic career, until I went to Lancaster, and I was 30 when I went to Lancaster.  So I spent the whole of my twenties not being quite sure, and t
h
erefore, I missed the golden years.  When I went to Lancaster in 1976, the system had already started to close down.  And people who are exactly the same age as I am, but who were appointed when they were in their early to mid-twenties, as a number of peo
ple were, experienced the expansion period, when everything seemed possible, and the money flowed, at least, that\rquote 
s what people tell me!  But I never experienced that.  It was always difficult, and you always had to fight for it, and you were always under some sort of pressure.  And it\rquote s been like that the whole of my time in universities.  So I\rquote 
ve never shared that sense which a number of older people have, and which even a number of my contemporaries have, if they were into the system earlier than I was, that everything that\rquote 
s happened since about the mid-seventies, has been some sort of aberration, and if only we could find the right government, we\rquote d get back to how it should be, you know.  I\rquote ve never felt that.  And so I think that was another reason for 
the relative ability to be resilient in those very difficult times in the eighties for sociology.
\par 
