 I knew that I wanted a career, and, as I said I think, before, only at the very early stages of being married, did I ever not have an income, and I really didn\rquote 
t like that, so I knew that I wanted to earn my own living, as it were.  I think I knew that I, if I was to pursue an academic career, it would make demands on my husband, in terms of restricting what he would do, and
